episodes.synopsis: A young man wants to trade a 1750 Blunderbuss gun for an engagement ring. A seller offers an ejection seat allegedly from a World War II fighter.
episodes.title: Brothels & Busses

episodes.synopsis: Rick refurbishes a gas pump with a bird's nest inside. Meanwhile, Corey takes a quiz after misidentifying a Fabergé crystal glass.
episodes.title: Rick's Big Bet

episodes.synopsis: When Rick and the Old Man buy an antique 19th-century wine maker, Chumlee wants to put it into action. Will he succeed and craft a Pawn Shop pinot?
episodes.title: Pawn Shop Pinot

episodes.synopsis: The Pawn Stars might buy a theater playbill from the night that Abraham Lincoln was assassinated, but first they must determine its authenticity.
episodes.title: Rick's Bad Day

episodes.synopsis: The Pawn Stars are presented with the most explosive item to ever walk through the door -- a pair of Soviet nuclear missile launch keys.
episodes.title: Big Guns

episodes.synopsis: Roar down the road with the Pawn Stars as they stumble upon a Down and Dirty custom motorcycle frame.
episodes.title: Bare Bones

episodes.synopsis: The Pawn Stars appraise a Colt .45 "peacemaker" revolver from the 1890s, Elvis Presley's medical records and photos taken during World War II.
episodes.title: Peacemaker

episodes.synopsis: Customers bring in a Civil War era drum and a uniform from a classic motorcycle club. Meanwhile, Chumlee fills in as a security guard.
episodes.title: Security

episodes.synopsis: Tools for killing vampires and conducting paranormal investigations find their way into the shop in this Halloween-themed episode.
episodes.title: Rick or Treat

episodes.synopsis: The Pawn Stars come across a classic car that may have belonged to gangster Bugsy Siegel and an Olympic torch from the 1984 Summer Games.
episodes.title: Blaze of Glory

episodes.synopsis: While searching for a night shift employee, the guys appraise a set of World War II bomb fins and a guitar signed by Crosby, Stills and Nash.
episodes.title: Crosby, Stills and Cash

episodes.synopsis: The Pawn Stars appraise two historical finds: a book signed by Charles Lindbergh and a German-issued medal commemorating the demise of the Lusitania.
episodes.title: That Sinking Feeling

episodes.synopsis: Rick negotiates for a signed copy of a memoir written by Dwight D. Eisenhower and weighs the value of a Civil War-era pistol.
episodes.title: Cool as Ike

episodes.synopsis: This week's finds include a book from the 15th century, a sitar and an ID card that belonged to legendary daredevil Evel Knievel.
episodes.title: Book 'Em Rick

episodes.synopsis: Rick gets a birthday surprise: a trip to Rock 'n' Roll Fantasy Camp. Back at the shop, the guys appraise an antique medical instrument.
episodes.title: Rick 'n' Roll

video.title: Pawn Stars: Collection
video.synopsis: The haggling never stops at the world-famous Las Vegas Gold & Silver Pawn Shop, which routinely gets vintage items and specialty pieces.
